{"lemma":"مَرْدُودُو","slug":"مَرْدُودُو","root":"ر.د.د","root_slug":"ر-د-د","root_link":"/words/roots/ر-د-د","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"مَرْدُود","root":"ردد","pos":"N","occurrence_count":2},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":2,"pos_tags":["adj","noun"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":3},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n15207"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D9%85%D9%8E%D8%B1%D9%92%D8%AF%D9%8F%D9%88%D8%AF%D9%8F%D9%88"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"adj","gloss":"passive participle of رَدَّ (radda); rejected"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"passive participle of رَدَّ (radda); rejected (Hadith terminology)"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"yield, pay-off, returns, revenue"}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Derived from the passive participle of the verb رَدَّ (radda, “to return something”)."},"ipa":["/mar.duːd/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n15207","headword_ar":"مَرْدُودٌ","root":"rd","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rad~N","text_ar":"رَدٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in three places. ―         -b2-  You say also, ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"laA xayora fiY qawolK maroduwdK wamurad~adK","text_ar":"لَا خَيْرَ فِى قَوْلٍ مَرْدُودٍ وَمُرَدَّدٍ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"There is no good in a saying rebutted and reiterated"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (A.) ―         -b3-  And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baAbN maroduwdN","text_ar":"بَابٌ مَرْدُودٌ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A door shut,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"closed; not opened."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh.) ―         -b4-  And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AimoraA^apN maroduwdapN","text_ar":"اِمْرَاَةٌ مَرْدُودَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A woman divorced;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T, S, * M, A, K; *) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rud~aY","text_ar":"رُدَّى","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (AA, K:) because she is sent back to the house of her parents. (A.) [In the present day, also applied to"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A woman taken back after divorce."},{"kind":"text","text":"] ―         -b5-  See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"murid~N","text_ar":"مُرِدٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":".       -A2-  Also an inf. n. [of an unusual form] of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rad~ahu","text_ar":"رَدَّهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (S, L, K.)"}],"source_refs":["AA","K"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}